        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 28 at 4:09PM MDT by NWS Albuquerque NM</headline>
        <description>At 409 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 6
miles southeast of Abbott, or 24 miles east of Springer, moving
southwest at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Abbott.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
